<br>
Cook,<br>
What you are describing with your example of the connotations my name brings to your mind is something that I have frequently had to  grapple with when I read what other vets say.  I have found that my first reading really isn't about what they have said as much as it is about what I have been through and therefore superimpose on what the other has said.  I cannot react upon my gut response because it may be harmful and downright wrong.  I have to reread after the gut has been purged and try to address what the other person is really saying.  I don't know if that is what discomforts you about my style of writing.  I don't know how to change my style.  It is part of me.  Having been in Nam I hate to tell a vet that my name is Betty because even for me the connotation is of the &quot;bouncing betty&quot;  that did so much damage to too many of our guys.  But, Betty is my first name so I'm stuck with it. I am not a destroyer of men.  I am not Dr. Betty, I don't have a doctorate and I am not a medical doctor.  I am not ant-vet even though as I said before, I have been hurt by the attitude of some veterans toward me who haven't even known me.<br><br>
I have posted a couple of times before the April post that you mentioned above.  Art was online at the time and I think you were too.  I used the name Betty.  I became friends with Doc Del bc. and had a few, not many conversations with Barry bc.  Both Doc Del and Barry wanted me to post more often but at that time I couldn't/wouldn't.  I wasn't emotionally ready to do this.  Doc Del's attempt to get me to post was to set up a thread calling for all women who were here to speak and if you find that you'll see he talks of RCW (Red Cross Workers) because he knew from our conversations that just as there are multiple branches of the armed forces and different jobs that each does within that branch, all of the women didn't do the same job or work for the same branch.  No women came forward.  The thread only has 2 posts.  Barry was pushy about trying to get me on-site and that is most likely the reason for the multiple times he talked to/about me.  What he couldn't do... somehow you guys have managed.  Or maybe I have finally just gotten to a point where I am finding I do have a voice afterall.<br><br>
I don't want to talk about Barry Spatz any more.   I don't like what I have been seeing going on here and some of the other recent threads.  I don't know what to believe any more than others who have commented on the derogatory posts attributed to Barry.  
<p><code>--   (Class Lass) </code><p>


